<br>
Then he compounds his stupidity by posting this guys ((annabolics) information on a public forum, so that the mob can flex their virtual muscles and start calling.  Now had Farhner (sp) gotten the information and called this guys parents or sent them a letter, that would have been the correct thing to do.  But by posting that information, he was wrong and anyone who harrasses or encourages harrassment is wrong.  You can try and justify if that he deserves it.  Yes Annabolic did deserve some sort of reprecussions for his actions but no way is this the correct way to do it.<br>
<br>
Let us remember that this all started because 1) you have a scammer running around 2) you have a greedy moron running around.  The victim laid down 90k he obviously couldn't afford to lose.  He puts up his &quot;prized&quot; helm in an attempt to win back the pp he had lost, knowing full well that there was a 50/50 chance of losing it.  He gets scammed and then comes to the boards and post private information, encouraging others, who haven't been scammed by this guy to jump on the band wagon.<br>
<br>
This Anabolic should be punished, through proper channels.  Yes they are slow, yes they aren't as much fun as say . . . getting to harrass someone....but sending out petitions to GMs, emails to Sony, and the one who got scammed speaking with his parents without sending the bored mobs on this guy, that would have been the correct way. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mackjon.f2s.com/poy3.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
